The paper deals with graph theory problems, specifically the Chinese Postman Problem and Euler trails, on directed graphs with colored arcs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the field of combinatorics (cs.CC) due to its focus on counting and optimization problems.
